            "id": "4573205",
            "title": "Carnival and Royal Caribbean lead a big jump in travel stocks after the Iran-U.S. ceasefire",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">The travel sector shot up on Wednesday after the U.S. and Iran agreed to a two-week, Pakistan-brokered ceasefire after days of escalating conflict and a Trump deadline. The deal pauses U.S. and Israeli strikes on Iran while talks continue, and it is tied to Iran ensuring safe, immediate reopening of the Strait of Hormuz. Notably, both sides are using the truce to negotiate a broader peace framework.</p>\n<p>Gainers in premarket action included cruise line stocks Carnival (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CCL\" title=\"Carnival Corporation &amp; plc\">CCL</a></span>) +10.2%, Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NCLH\" title=\"Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd.\">NCLH</a></span>) +8.7%, Royal Caribbean (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RCL\" title=\"Royal Caribbean Cruises Ltd.\">RCL</a></span>) +7.7%, Viking Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VIK\" title=\"Viking Holdings Ltd\">VIK</a></span>) +5.9%, and Lindblad Expeditions (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LIND\" title=\"Lindblad Expeditions Holdings, Inc.\">LIND</a>) +5.4%. The sharp decline in oil prices from record levels boosted the cruise line names. Hotel operators Hyatt Hotels (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/H\" title=\"Hyatt Hotels Corporation\">H</a>) +3.0%, Marriott International (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MAR\" title=\"Marriott International, Inc.\">MAR</a>) +4.9%, InterContinental Hotels Group (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IHG\" title=\"InterContinental Hotels Group PLC\">IHG</a>) +6.8%, and Hilton Worldwide (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HLT\" title=\"Hilton Worldwide Holdings Inc.\">HLT</a>) +2.8% also showed gains, while Airbnb (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ABNB\" title=\"Airbnb, Inc.\">ABNB</a>) rose 3.3% and Booking Holdings (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BKNG\" title=\"Booking Holdings Inc.\">BKNG</a>) rallied 5.2%.</p>\n<p>Wynn Resorts (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WYNN\" title=\"Wynn Resorts, Limited\">WYNN</a>), which has a project in the United Arab Emirates impacted by Middle East travel trends, was up 3.9% in the early session. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
